    <article title="Liver Disease at VA">

      <faq-menu>
        <title>Liver Disease at VA</title>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <title>Where can I get information about benefits?</title>
            <answer>
              <p>There are several different sources of benefits for veterans:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Social security</li>
                <li>Service-connected pensions</li>
                <li>Non-service-connected pensions</li>
                <li>Disabled American Veterans</li>
                <li>Veterans of Foreign Wars</li>
                <li>American Legion</li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                Getting service-connection for HCV infection is difficult.  Most people cannot prove that they got HCV during their military service.
              </p>
              <p>
                For more information, go to
                <ilink-sref ref="www.va.gov/health/default.asp">VA Health Care Benefits</ilink-sref>
                .
              </p>
            </answer>
          </li>
          <li>
            <title>Will I have to pay anything for my care and medications at VA?</title>
            <answer>
              <p>
                At VA, some Veterans are required to pay a copayment for VA healthcare services. Take a look at the VA Benefits website for information on
                <ilink-sref ref="www.va.gov/HEALTHBENEFITS/cost/copays.asp">how copayment eligibility is determined</ilink-sref>
                and
                <ilink-sref ref="www.va.gov/healthbenefits/cost/copay_rates.asp">copay rates for healthcare services and medications</ilink-sref>
                .
              </p>
            </answer>
          </li>
        </ul>

